> Dear Simon,
>
> I am writing because you are the maintainer of CRAN package "lulcc".
>
> There is an error when I check "lulcc" with the development version of the
> "raster" package. The reason for this seems to be the changes that I made
> in the raster::crosstab function. I made these changes to make it more
> consistent. See the discussion here:
> https://github.com/rspatial/raster/issues/24
>
> This is the error:
>
>> library(lulcc)
>> obs <- ObsLulcRasterStack(x=pie,
> +                    pattern="lu",
> +                    categories=c(1,2,3),
> +                    labels=c("forest","built","other"),
> +                    t=c(0,6,14))
>>
>> crossTabulate(x=obs, times=c(0,14))
> Error: $ operator is invalid for atomic vectors
>
>> traceback()
> 7: which(ct$Var1 == cat1 & ct$Var2 == cat2)
> 6: .local(x, y, ...)
> 5: crossTabulate(x = x[[ix1]], y = x[[ix2]], categories = x@categories,
>        labels = x@labels)
> 4: crossTabulate(x = x[[ix1]], y = x[[ix2]], categories = x@categories,
>        labels = x@labels)
> 3: .local(x, y, ...)
> 2: crossTabulate(x = obs, times = c(0, 14))
> 1: crossTabulate(x = obs, times = c(0, 14))
